<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,402,748]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,291,402,428]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Bionomics:</emphasis>
Univoltine. The species inhabits dry steppe biotopes on medium elevations (
<quantity box="[1255,1423,402,428]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="m" value="1350.0" valueMax="1700.0" valueMin="1000.0">1000-1700 m</quantity>
). Moths flying from May to June. Larvae feed on 
<taxonomicName box="[717,813,442,467]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Phlomis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[717,813,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Phlomis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp.
</paragraph>
